						<summary>

						<p>Same wall.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">No King: No date.</hi></p>						

						<p>This inscription appears to be incomplete.</p>						

						<p>It states that a certain Perunambigaḷ, belonging to the <hi rend="italic">santāna</hi> (lineage or family) of certain Śāttaṉār who had the titles of <hi rend="italic">Muttamiḻ Āchāryar</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Tamiḻ-karaikaṇḍa</hi> and who was a member of the <hi rend="italic">Gaḍikai</hi> (Skt. <hi rend="italic">Ghaṭikā,</hi> a learned assembly) of Kāvaṉūr <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Poyyāmoḻimaṅgalam in Kōṉāsura-nāḍu in Śeṅgāṭṭuk-kōṭṭam owned Poyyāmoḻimaṅgalam as his <hi rend="italic">kāṇi.</hi> </p>						

						</summary>
					</msContents>
